place.name: WINSLADE
place.gazetteerText: WINSLADE, a parish, with Kempshot tything, in Basingstoke district, Hants; 3 miles S by E of Basingstoke r. station. Post town, Basingstoke. Acres, 1,235. Real property, £1,630. Pop., 183. Houses, 31. The manor belongs to Lord Bolton. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Winchester. Value, £164.* Patron, Lord Bolton. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
